-- Zambian Police Arrest Son of Former President for Corruption
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-06-01T11:07:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-01/zambian-police-arrest-son-of-former-president-for-corruption.html
Zambian police arrested the son of
former President Rupiah Banda on suspicion of soliciting a bribe
from an Italian construction company, police spokeswoman
Namukolo Kasumpa said.  Andrew Banda has been charged with “corrupt practices and
being in possession of property suspected to be the proceeds of
a crime,” Kasumpa said today in phone interview from Lusaka,
the capital. He was released on bail, she said.  Banda is the oldest son of the former president, who lost
am election in September to  Michael Sata . Sata promised to
crackdown on corruption in the copper-rich southern African
nation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
